{"article_id":"VcdNv7hBxEzF7FzZ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"As President Obama prepares to head to Colorado on Wednesday","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to push gun control legislation ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"some are calling into question the validity of a key statistic","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"he ' s using","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"to tout his message on near-universal background checks .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"During several speeches , Obama has said","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"40 percent of all gun purchases were made","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"without a background check .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"But that number is nearly two decades old","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"and comes from a poll with a relatively tiny sample size .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Gun rights groups like the National Rifle Association , as well as The Washington Post ' s \" Fact Checker , \" are calling out the president ' s stat ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"his numbers on background checks need a background check of their own .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"During a speech last week , Obama asked ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"\" Why wouldn ' t we want to make it more difficult for a dangerous person to get his or her hand on a gun ?","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Why wouldn ' t we want to close the loophole","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"that allows as many as 40 percent of all gun purchases to take place","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"without a background check ?","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"Why wouldn ' t we do that ? \"","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"The oft-cited figure ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"it turns out ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"was pulled from a 1997 study","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"done by the National Institute of Justice .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"In the study , researchers estimated","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"about 40 percent of all firearm sales took place through people other than licensed gun dealers .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"The conclusion was based on data from a 1994 survey of 2,568 households .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"Of those , only 251 people answered the question","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"about where they got their guns .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"PolitiFact tracked down the co-author of the study , Duke University professor Philip Cook ,","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"and asked him","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"if he thought","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"the 40 percent estimate is accurate .","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"\" The answer is I have no idea , \"","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"Cook reportedly told PolitiFact .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"\" This survey was done almost 20 years ago . \"","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"The National Rifle Association has questioned the 40 percent claim","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"and says","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"it ' s a misrepresentation by gun control advocates","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"to trump up support for universal background checks .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"Another problem with the study is the sample size , 251 people ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"which is relatively small ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"and the data is open to interpretation .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"\" With this sample size , the 95 percent confidence interval will be plus or minus six percentage points , \"","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"The Washington Post fact-checker wrote on Tuesday .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"\" Moreover , when asked","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"whether the respondent brought from a licensed firearms dealer ,","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"the possible answers included ' probably was/think so ' and ' probably not , '","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"leaving open the possibility","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"the purchaser was mistaken . \"","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"When all of the \" yes \" and \" probably was \" answers were added together ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"35.7 percent of those asked said","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"they did not receive a gun from a licensed firearms dealer .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"If you round the number up ,","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"it becomes 40 percent","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"but","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"because the sample size is so small ,","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"rounding the number down to 30 percent could also be accurate ,","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"the paper noted .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"\" While slagging the president may be good for business ,","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"the effect of","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"( the newspaper ' s )","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"false ruling is to undermine legitimate efforts","depth":16},{"id":62,"text":"to keep the public safe ,","depth":16},{"id":63,"text":"and to obscure the real enemy of reliable data on gun violence , \"","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"Tommy Christopher of Mediaite wrote in a rebuttal Tuesday .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"\" It is possible to conclude that as few as 26.4 % of gun owners in that study 'purchased ' their gun","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"without a background check , 20.4 %","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"if you factor in the margin of error , \"","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"The administration has not responded to questions","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"surrounding the number","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"and why they continue to use it","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"to promote their gun control measures .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"The president is n't the only one","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"who 's used the 40 percent figure","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"to make a point .","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"Many others","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"stumping for the cause","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"have pulled from the same info pile .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"On Jan. 24 , New York Sen. Kirsten Gillibrand stated the importance of background checks during a television interview .","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"\" The background checks bill is vitally important .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"It ' s going to basically say","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"you can ' t buy guns","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"without getting a background check .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Today , about 40 percent of guns are purchased","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"without a background check . \"","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"Seven months earlier , New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg used the same statistic","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"to skewer the National Rifle Association","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"following the Colorado movie theatre massacre .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"\" There ' s a loophole","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"where you can sell guns","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"without a background check , \"","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"he said last year , on July 22 .","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"\" Forty percent of guns are sold that way . \"","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"For months , both sides of the debate on gun control","depth":4},{"id":95,"text":"- from the local level all the way up to the national level --","depth":4},{"id":96,"text":"have accused the other of inflating figures and manipulating data .","depth":3},{"id":97,"text":"Obama ,","depth":5},{"id":98,"text":"in using an array of stats and studies and polls ,","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"has tried to make the case","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"that the Senate is considering common-sense proposals","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"that most Americans support .","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"Amid resistance from some lawmakers , the president is ramping up his campaign for the legislation .","depth":4},{"id":103,"text":"He plans to visit Denver on Wednesday ,","depth":4},{"id":104,"text":"followed by a stop next Monday in Hartford , Conn. , the state","depth":5},{"id":105,"text":"that was the site of the deadly mass shooting in Newtown in December .","depth":5}],"relat